{{Infobox organization |name = Bangladesh Public Service Commission |image = Government Seal of Bangladesh.svg |image_border = |size = 100px |alt = |caption = [[Government Seal of Bangladesh]] |map = |msize = |malt = |mcaption = |abbreviation = BPSC |motto = |formation = |extinction = |type = [[Governmental]] |status = Constitutional Body |purpose = Recruitment |headquarters = [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]] |location = |coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template --> |region_served = Bangladesh |members = |language = Bengali |leader_title = Chairman |leader_name = Dr Mohammad Sadik |main_organ = |parent_organization = |affiliations = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = {{Official website|http://www.bpsc.gov.bd/}} |remarks = }}
'''Bangladesh Public Service Commission''' ({{lang-bn|বাংলাদেশ সরকারী কর্ম কমিশন}}) is quasi judicial constitutional body established in 1972. The commission is responsible for the recruitment of civil service servants in Bangladesh government.<ref>{{cite web|title=Who We Are|url=http://www.bpsc.gov.bd/platform/node/10.bpsc2012.pml|website=bpsc.gov.bd|accessdate=23 February 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303215841/http://www.bpsc.gov.bd/platform/node/10.bpsc2012.pml|archive-date=2016-03-03|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref> It was formed by Section 137 of Part IX, Chapter II of the [[Constitution of Bangladesh]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://bdlaws.minlaw.gov.bd/sections_detail.php?id=367&sections_id=24697|title=Establishment of commissions|last=Constitution of Bangladesh|first=|date=|website=bdlaws.minlaw.gov.bd|publisher=Peoples' Republic of Bangladesh|pages=Part IX, Chapter II, Section 137|access-date=2016-09-20}}</ref>
The commission started as public service commission in 1926 during British India, it was later Known as East Pakistan Public service commission after the partition of India. After the Independence of Bangladesh it was established as Bangladesh Public Service Commission in 1972.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bangladesh Public Service Commission|url=http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Bangladesh_Public_Service_Commission|website=en.banglapedia.org|publisher=Banglapedia|accessdate=23 February 2016}}</ref> For a while it used the [[Chummery House]] as its headquarters.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Chummery_House|title=Chummery House - Banglapedia|website=en.banglapedia.org|language=en|access-date=2017-07-13}}</ref> It is responsible for holding [[BCS Examination|Bangladesh Civil Service (BCS) Examination]] and publishing its results.<ref>{{cite web|title=Listen to them!|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/star-weekend/education/listen-them-171286|website=thedailystar.net|publisher=The Daily Star|accessdate=23 February 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=34th BCS final results published|url=http://en.prothom-alo.com/bangladesh/news/77353/34th-BCS-final-results-published|website=en.prothom-alo.com|publisher=Prothom Alo|accessdate=23 February 2016}}</ref>
