{{redirect|COTT|the beverage company|Cott}}
The '''Copyright Music Organisation of Trinidad and Tobago''' ('''COTT''') is a [[non-profit organization|non-profit]] association representing people in the [[music industry]] of [[Trinidad and Tobago]].<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=7CVBAQAAIAAJ&q=Copyright+Music+Organisation+of+Trinidad+and+Tobago&dq=Copyright+Music+Organisation+of+Trinidad+and+Tobago&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjUpKPtk4jTAhWJL8AKHTQmC7EQ6AEIKDAD|title=Journal of the Copyright Society of the U.S.A.|last=|first=|date=2003-01-01|publisher=The Society|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=381|language=en}}</ref> COTT was incorporated in 1984 and began operating in 1985.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=sHtOAAAAYAAJ&q=Copyright+Music+Organisation+of+Trinidad+and+Tobago&dq=Copyright+Music+Organisation+of+Trinidad+and+Tobago&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiw7qK0lIjTAhUkLsAKHRz-AJIQ6AEILDAE|title=Copyrights: A Choice of No Choice for Artists and Third World Countries|last=Smiers|first=Joost|last2=Förster|first2=Larissa|date=1999-01-01|publisher=Köppe|year=|isbn=9783896452436|location=|pages=9|language=en}}</ref>

Before COTT was established its current role was carried out by the [[United Kingdom|United Kingdom's]] [[Performing Right Society]].

