The '''Regional Council of French Guiana''' ([[French language|French]]: ''Conseil régional de la Guyane'') was the elected assembly, or [[Regional Council (France)|regional council]] of [[French Guiana]].
The Regional Council was composed of thirty-one members, presided over by the [[President of the Regional Council of French Guiana]]. The council was headquartered in [[Cité Administrative Régionale]], near the outskirts of [[Cayenne]]. It ceased to exist on January 1, 2016.
